In this article, President Trump addresses a gathering of women from across his administration and thanks them for their work. He acknowledges the accomplishments of women in the workforce, mentioning the lowest women's unemployment rate in 17 years and the record high number of women in the workforce. Trump also highlights the lowest African American unemployment rate ever recorded. He discusses the success of the tax cuts and the positive impact it has had on individuals and the stock market. Trump emphasizes the importance of reducing regulations and mentions the positive effects it has had on job creation and economic growth. He also mentions efforts to address the drug addiction problem in the country. Trump concludes by expressing his appreciation for the women in his administration and their contributions.